  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba3\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0b95\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Demand to increase electricity bills",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Janaka Ratnayake, chairman of the Public Utilities Commission, said today (27) that the increase in electricity tariff should not exceed 57 per cent and that it was determined to know the views of the public on the proposed tariff revision.",
        "He also said that the Public Utilities Commission has sought the approval of the Ceylon Electricity Board for an 82 percent tariff increase under Section 30 of the Ceylon Electricity Act No. 20 of 2009.",
        "He added that the tariff increase should not exceed 57 per cent as a concession to the majority of household electricity consumers.",
        "He pointed out that there are 3.14 million household consumers who use less than 60 units of electricity per month, which is about 50 per cent of the total household electricity consumption.",
        "He also noted that the Commission had observed that the conditions imposed on the Ceylon Electricity Board with the 2014 tariff revision had not yet been met.",
        "The Commission has asked the Electricity Board to accept in dollars the monthly electricity bill from companies that earn in dollars.",
        "Information on the proposed tariff revision (Public Consultation Document) has been published on the website of the Public Utilities Commission of Sri Lanka.",
        "The Commission has announced that written comments can be submitted by email or fax until July 18, 2022."
      ],
